commitResults.messageTitle: Update product scope and user stories
commitResults.messageBody:
The current product scope and user stories is for address book 3.

The product scope and user stories should be about our project.

Let's update the product scope and user stories to match our project.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add use case for adding a contact
Update user guide for add contact

commitResults.messageBody:
The current add command is ambiguous as it does not state whether
it adds a task or a contact.

Let's update the add command with a new name and syntax to show
what it adds a contact instead.

The current list command is ambiguous as it does not state whether
it lists a task or a contact.

Let's update the list command with a new name and syntax to show
what it lists contacts instead.

The current delete command is ambiguous as it does not state whether
it deletes a task or a contact.

Let's update the delete command with a new name and syntax to show
that it deletes a contact instead.

The current edit command is ambiguous as it does not state whether
it deletes a task or a contact.

Let's update the edit command with a new name and syntax to show
that it edits a contact instead.

The current find command is ambiguous as it does not state whether
it finds a task or a contact.

Let's update the find command with a new name and syntax to show
that it finds a contact instead.

Contact commands' names and synatax are updated but not
the documentation. This is because Intellij does not
refactor header comments.

Let's update the documentation to reflect the changes.

commitResults.messageBody:
There is no way for the user to edit their tasks after adding it
to the task list.

Let's add an edit command to allow the user to do so.

There is no way to see other type of lists other than the list of
contacts.

Let's add tabs so that we can switch tabs to see another type of
list.

Tabs allow us to see the list that we are currently interested in
at the moment.

commitResults.messageBody:
There is no GUI to display the task list after adding tasks to it.

Let's make a GUI to display the task list.

Use of a list view and card allows the user to see tasks
row by row.

There is no GUI to display the tag list after adding a tag.

Let's add a GUI to display the tag list.

Use of a flow pane allows the user to add as many tags as they
want without the tags exceeding the width of the pane.

Users have no way to see the deadline.

Let's modfiy the GUI to be able to display the deadline.

commitResults.messageTitle: Modify edit task command to also copy deadlines,tags and isDone
commitResults.messageBody:
Edit task command can only copy description.

Let's allow edit task command to also copy the remaining fields.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove duplicate methods in test case
Fix edit task command not allowing deadlines to be edited
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadlines cannot be edited in edit task command.

Let's fix edit task command to allow tasks to be edited.

commitResults.messageTitle: Change edit task command to copy isDone value as well
commitResults.messageBody:
Edit task command always sets isDone to false as editTaskDescriptor
was not copying taskToEdit's isDone.

Let's change edit task command to copy taskToEdit's isDone instead.

The user is unable to see the most urgent tasks to complete.

Let's add a sort by deadline command to allow the user to do so.
This allows the user to see the list of tasks starting from the
earliest to the latest deadline.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update storage to store status of sort by deadline
commitResults.messageBody:
Each time the user exits and starts the app, the task list is no
longer sorted when the user adds a new task or edits the deadline.

Users who prefer a sort by deadline order will need to sort on
starting the app each time.

Let's update storage to store the status of sort by deadline such
that the user only needs to sort once when they prefer the sort by
deadline order.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add sort by id and improve code quality for sort by deadline
commitResults.messageBody:
There is no way for the user to return the list back to the
original state after using sort by deadline.

Let's add a way for the user to do so through the sort by id
command.

Let's,
* give each task an Id class to manage their id
* make each id comparable to allow sorting by id
* update edit task command to copy ids

commitResults.messageTitle: Add storage for id, sort by id and update other commands with id
commitResults.messageBody:
Each time the user exits and starts the app, the task list is no
longer sorted by their previous id as a new id is given to each of
them.

Users who prefer a sort by id order will not be able to retain the
initial id order.

Let's update storage to store the id of tasks and to know when to
sort by id.

Additionally, the ids of new tasks will be incorrect since
id count is always initialized to 0 but some task could already
have that id.

Let's also update id to correctly initialize id count.

commitResults.messageBody:
The current way of testing commands is by seeing the changes
through the GUI. This is tedious as the commands need to be typed
manually.

Let's automate this process by adding test cases.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix style and documentation for classes in main

commitResults.messageBody:
When the user finishes a project, they will have to manually
delete the tasks, contacts and tags associated with it one by one.

Let's instead provide a way to delete all these information by
simply specifying the tag to be deleted through the delete all
command.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bug where delete all fails for multiple tags
commitResults.messageBody:
Delete all only deletes the task if the task has only one tag.
For tasks with multiple tags, delete all only removes the tags.
This does not take into account the scenario where the task has
no tags left after removing all tags.

Let's update the delete all command to delete the tasks with no
tags after removing their tags.

It can be confusing for new users when the messages displayed use
tags while the commands and user guide use labels.

Let's rename tag to label for the user messages to prevent
confusion.

commitResults.messageBody:
There are no mark and unmark task commands.

Allowing users to mark their tasks as completed or incomplete will help them keep track of what tasks they have not done.

Let's add mark and unmark task commands.

Add contact command and edit contact command does not allow adding of remark to a person in address book.

A remark is more user-friendly because users are able to note down important things about a person.

Let's allow adding of remark to a person in address book.

Mark and unmark task commands do not change the gui immediately after being executed.

Updating the commands gets rid of this bug.

Let's update mark and unmark task commands.

Task list is not stored.

The user needs the data to be stored to use the address book regularly.

Let's store the task list.

Update how task status is displayed in result box
commitResults.messageBody:
Task completion status is shown as true/false.

This is not intuitive for less-technical users.

Let's display as completed/not completed instead.

Task::getStatus() is used to get completion status of task.

isArchive field is going to be added to task which may cause ambiguity
in what "status" refers to.

Let's:
- Refactor Task::getStatus to Task::getCompletionStatus
- Refactor Task::getStatusForDisplay to
Task::getCompletionStatusForDisplay
- Refactor code in TaskCard to be more concise
- Declare "magic constant" colour hex-codes as variables
